Two Marlian music signees, Oniyide Azeez (Zinoleesky) and Mohbad (Ilerioluwa Oladimeji) have been arrested by officials of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA). NDLEA stormed their home in the Lekki area of Lagos to whisk them away. In video uploaded on Instagram, the agents were seen hitting the artists and forcing them into a waiting bus.   BREAKING: Buhari arrives Nasarawa for official visit     Russia has declared war on Ukraine, Envoy tells UN Security…     JUST IN: Russia bombs Ukraine as full invasion begins   The entire scene was chaotic as some ladies with the artists at the time of the arrest were heard screaming and condemning the violence meted out on the music stars. Reacting to this Marlian music Boss, Naira Marley wrote on Instagram: “I’m so f**king angry right now”. As at the time of filing this report, there has been no word out from NDLEA on the reason for their arrest.